Because I believe that AACN shouldn't just be about parties:

Two new job opportunities at the Chemistry of Life Processes Institute.

Chemistry of Life Processes Institute Temporary Financial Assistant
Quantitative Bio-element Imaging Center Temporary Research Assistant
Chemistry of Life Processes Institute Temporary Financial Assistant
This is full-time position (37.50 hours per week / 9am – 5pm / M-F).
Paying approximately $17.60 per hour.
Campus: Evanston.

This position has an approximate start date of 10/1/14.
This position has an approximate end date 12/31/14.

The Financial Assistant is responsible for providing financial and accounting support to the Chemistry Life Processes Business Manager in areas related to purchasing, recharge activities, reconciliation and records management for sponsored and nonsponsored accounts. 

Responsibilities include:
Processing requisitions, vouchers, expense reports, wire transfers, and journals;
Assisting with vendor relations including issues related to vendor codes, receipts, invoices and credits;
Processing NUCore orders on behalf of nine recharge facilities.
Assisting with post award activities for sponsored research as needed.
Reconciling and updating financial worksheets;
Support Northwestern Physical Science-Oncology Center (PSOC)

Skills Required:
Experience with NUFinancials and Cognos;
Knowledge of NUCore preferred;
Knowledge of Northwestern’s financial management policies preferred;
Excellent attention to detail and organizational skills;
Excellent written and oral communication skills;
Critical thinking skills with excellent follow through;
Customer service oriented.

Job Qualifications:
A bachelor's degree or the equivalent combination of education, training and experience;
Strong writing skills;
High level of organizational skills and attention to detail;
Diligent and can work independently;
Experience working with confidential information;
Professionalism;
Flexibility, adaptability in a fast paced environment.
Software Required:
Advanced knowledge of MS Office Suite 2010 (Excel, Word, Outlook and PowerPoint).

To Apply:
Submit application through Northwestern University’s online career websitehttp://www.northwestern.edu/hr/careers/
Search for Job ID: 23909
Please attach a cover letter for full consideration for the temporary opportunity of Temporary Financial Assistant.
As per Northwestern University policy, this position requires a criminal background check. Successful applicants will need to submit to a criminal background check prior to employment.
Northwestern University is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative Action Employer of all protected classes including veterans and individuals with disabilities.

QBIC - Temporary - Research Technologist
This is full-time position (40 hours per week / evening and weekend hours may be necessary).
Paying approximately $15.00 per hour.

Campus: Evanston.
This position has an approximate start date of ASAP.
This position has an end date of approximately TBD.

The Quantitative Bio-element Imaging Center (QBIC) at Northwestern University is seeking exceptional candidates for a research technologist to meet the expanding needs of QBIC. QBIC is a shared instrumentation research facility that focuses on trace metal analysis and quantitative elemental mapping of a wide variety of sample types ranging from single cells to complex materials. The center is part of the transdisciplinary Chemistry of Life Processes Institute whose mission is to use interdisciplinary approaches to generate transformative scientific advances in ways that traditional, single-discipline methodology cannot.

Specific Responsibilities: 
Improve and develop analytical techniques to meet the expanding needs of QBIC uses;
Provide instrument training and support for customer-run applications in inductively coupled plasma-mass spectrometry (ICP-MIS);
HPLC and laser ablation, microwave digestion, atomic absorption spectroscopy, and multi-photon confocal microscopy;
Perform sample processing for customers using for customers using various analytical techniques;
Support development of technical papers, posters and other internal/external documents and communications, as needed;
Maintain records and lab environment to comply with regulatory requirements and standard operating procedures;
Maintain and service instruments and other lab equipment as needed;
Assist in customer billing and recharge services;
Perform other duties as assigned.

Qualifications Required:
A bachelor's degree in Chemistry, Biology, Biochemistry, Materials Science or related field or the equivalent combination of education, training and experience;
Experience in instrumental and analytical methods, experimental design, and computer analysis;
Proficient in sample preparation for trace metal analysis, spectroscopic technique, mass spectrometry and chromatography;
Mechanically incline in troubleshooting and maintaining analytical instruments;
Excellent communication skills and proficiency with MS Office and Adobe software;
Must be able to stand continuously for up to 8 hours, and lift up to 50 lobs;
Excellent customer service skills;
Excellent organizational skills;
High attention to detail.
Preferred Qualifications:
Master’s degree in Chemistry, Biology, Biochemistry, Materials Science, or related field;
Experience with one or more of the following: ICP-MS, GFAAS, ICP-OES, AA, Microwave Digestion, Confocal Microscopy;
Proficiency with Excel Macros, MatLab, and advanced statistical analysis programs.

Software Required:
MS Office suite 2010 (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook);
Adobe software suites.

To Apply:
Submit application through Northwestern University’s online career websitehttp://www.northwestern.edu/hr/careers/
Search for Job ID: 23864
